# SKILL CREATION INSTRUCTIONS

## STEP 1: Create Directory Structure

```
EXECUTE Bash WITH "mkdir -p .claude/skills/your-skill-name"
```

## STEP 2: Copy Template

```
EXECUTE Bash WITH "cp .claude/skills/skills.template .claude/skills/your-skill-name/SKILL.md"
```

## STEP 3: Update Frontmatter

EDIT frontmatter WITH actual_values FOR: - name: "your-skill-name" (kebab-case, matches directory) - description: "Clear description of what skill teaches and when to use" - allowed-tools: "Tools Claude can use (if restricting)" - model: "Specific model (if needed)"

## STEP 4: Define Core Knowledge

REPLACE template_concepts WITH domain_concepts

FOR EACH concept IN domain_knowledge:
ADD definition
ADD practical_examples
ADD relationship_to_other_concepts

## STEP 5: Document Step-by-Step Process

CREATE detailed_workflow FOR skill_application

FOR EACH step IN workflow:
SPECIFY action
PROVIDE implementation_details
DEFINE expected_output

## STEP 6: Add Examples

CREATE multiple_examples WITH varying_complexity

FOR EACH example:
DESCRIBE scenario
SHOW application_code
SPECIFY expected_outcome

## STEP 7: Progressive Disclosure (If Skill Complex)

IF skill_content > 500_lines:
CREATE additional_files: - advanced-patterns.md - examples.md - troubleshooting.md

    REFERENCE additional_files FROM SKILL.md:
        "For advanced patterns, see [advanced-patterns.md](./advanced-patterns.md)"

## STEP 8: Test Skill

CREATE test_task THAT should_trigger_skill
EXECUTE task WITH Claude
ANALYZE IF skill_was_invoked
IF skill_not_applied_correctly:
REFINE description OR domain_specification
ITERATE TO STEP 3

## STEP 9: Cleanup

DELETE ".claude/skills/skills.template"

VALIDATION GATE: Creation Workflow Complete
✅ All steps documented
✅ Testing procedure defined
✅ Progressive disclosure explained
✅ Cleanup specified

